race.description: Newmarket & Baker Group Cup Nov 21st Hcp (C1)
race.comment: BUNKER JAKO (1) resumes off a narrow defeat at Hobart in stronger. Won his Maiden here on debut prior and has warmed up for this with easy trial wins at the track. He will be naturally improved and is going to take some stopping. PRINCE OF KHATUN (5) peaks and has been nudged out twice here since the easy Maiden win on the synthetic. He's fast and can clear the awkward gate. Keeps Byrne Burke, and she's flying. A threat. STAR FORTIAN (11) was backed off the map on the synthetic first up and ran the Maidens off their feet. Was plainer here following, but will improve on that. She can use the inside barrier and will carry just 52.5kgs with the claim. CELTIC ROSE (7) carries the same weight and will build on her heavily-bet Maiden win this track/trip.
